{{Infobox Islands | name = Tane Island | image_name = BoraboraISS006-E-39815.PNG | image_caption = The Bora Bora Group. | native_name = | native_name_link = English | nickname = | location = Pacific Ocean | coordinates = {{coord|16.450|S|151.763|W|type:isle_region:PF|display=title}} | archipelago = [[Society Islands]] | total_islands = | major_islands = | area_km2 = 0.014 | highest_mount = | elevation_m = 0 | country = France | country_admin_divisions_title = [[Communes of France|Commune]] | country_admin_divisions = [[Bora Bora Commune]] | country_admin_divisions_title_2 = Island Group | country_admin_divisions_2 = [[Bora Bora]] | country_capital_city = | country_largest_city = Tane | country_largest_city_population = 0 | country_leader_title = | country_leader_name = |population = 0 | population_as_of = 2016 | density_km2 = 0 | ethnic_groups = | additional_info = }}
'''Motu Tane''' (which in Tahitian translates as Man's Island), is a {{convert|9.6|acre|km2|3|abbr=on|adj=on}} [[private island]] in the [[lagoon]] of [[Bora Bora]] in [[French Polynesia]]. It is the located between [[Paahi (Bora Bora)|Paahi]], and [[Pitoraverahi (Bora Bora)|Pitoraverahi]].
==History== Motu Tane is well known in Bora Bora as having been [[Paul-Emile Victor]]'s home. Paul-Emile Victor was the famous French polar explorer and author and chose as his personal paradise refuge Motu Tane in Bora Bora, to live a peaceful and secluded life.
The island has coconut groves, encircled by a white sand beach with just beyond Polynesia's sparkling turquoise blue waters. in 1997, it was purchased by [[NARS Cosmetics|François Nars]], artistic director of the well-known cosmetic brand that he founded and carries his own name.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.architecturaldigest.com/gallery/francois-nars-is-selling-his-island-in-bora-bora| title= Nars Island| accessdate=July 28, 2017}}</ref>
==Administration== The island is part of [[Bora Bora Commune]].
==Tourism== The island is up for sale <ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.privateislandsonline.com/south-pacific/frenchpolynesia/motu-tane2| title= Vladi real estate| accessdate=July 28, 2017}}</ref>
==Transportation==
After arriving in [[Fa'a'ā International Airport]], an [[Air Tahiti]] inter-island flight (50 minutes) will bring you to [[Bora Bora Airport]].
There, you will need to hire a boat at the [[Rent-a-boat]] Office.
