''This article is about fictional TV and radio stations that have used these call letters. For the real life radio station that currently uses these call letters, see [[WWEN (FM)|WWEN]].''
'''WWEN''' is an [[United States|American]] broadcast [[call sign]] for various fictional [[television station|television]] and [[radio station]]s depicted in various [[American television]] shows and movies. The call sign had not been assigned to a real-life TV or radio station in America until 2008.<ref>{{FML|WWEN}}. Retrieved 2010-12-27.</ref>
==Appearances== *The radio station at the end of the movie ''[[Across The Universe (film)|Across The Universe]]''. *A television station in the movie ''[[The Ref]]''. *A television station shown in the beginning of the movie ''[[Gone Baby Gone]]''. *A television station from the [[soap opera]] ''[[Days of Our Lives]]''. *A [[public-access television|public-access]] [[cable television]] station in the movie ''[[To Die For]]''. *A TV station in two episodes of ''[[Wings (NBC TV series)|Wings]]''. In Season 3, Episode 5, "If Elected, I Will Not Live," WWEN is a sponsor of a town council candidate debate between Roy Biggins and Fay Cochran. And in Season 4, Episode 4, "Blackout Buggins," a WWEN sports anchor jokes about Roy Biggins passing out while attempting to sing the national anthem at Fenway Park. *A [[CNBC]] News affiliate in the [[The Finale (Seinfeld)|final episode of Seinfeld]]. *The radio station in the ''[[Empty Nest]]'' episode "Talk, Talk, Talk."
